Silverman&rsquo;s rule of thumb for kernel density estimation bandwidth selection:
$$ h = 0.9 \cdot \min ( \hat{\sigma}, IQR/1.35 ) n^{-1/5} $$ Reference B. W. Silverman “Density Estimation for Statistics and Data Analysis” (1986) // Publisher: Chapman &amp; Hall, London.
